FBIS4-43011 "drweu112__a94037" FBIS-WEU-94-112-A Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 ANNEX Italy & Vatican City Government Begins Aid Program for Rwandan Refugees Government Begins Aid Program for Rwandan Refugees BR0306101594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 2136 GMT 2 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR0306101594 Rome ANSAMAIL Database English BFN [Unattributed article: "Rwanda/Italy: Emergency Aid to Refugees"] [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 2 -- Some 30 tonnes of emergency aid for Rwanda will be flown on Friday [3 June] from Italy to the Ugandan town of Entebbe, where it will be distributed to refugees from the Rwandan civil war, the Foreign Ministry said on Thursday. Another plane with a further 30 tonnes of aid will fly to Bujumbura, Burundi, for refugees there. Medical equipment provided by Italy arrived in Burundi today, and another consignment will be sent to the Ugandan capital Kampala within the next few days. These latest initiatives are part of an emergency programme for a total of almost ten billion lire (6.2 million dollars) financed by the Foreign Ministry's cooperation department.
